# Conclusion

This investigation demonstrates the effectiveness of host-centric threat hunting using Splunk and Zeek telemetry. By correlating activity across DNS, HTTP, FTP, and SSH logs, analysts can build comprehensive behavioral profiles of internal systems, improving visibility into network activity and strengthening incident detection capabilities.

The project highlights practical techniques for multi-protocol analysis that are commonly used in Security Operations Centers (SOCs) to identify abnormal behavior and investigate potential security incidents.
